    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why Edge Computing Matters</h2>

      <div class="reasons-grid">
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>üèÉ Speed</h3>
          <p><strong>10-50x faster response times</strong> by processing near users instead of across the globe.</p>
          <p class="impact">Impact: Better UX, higher conversion rates, reduced bounce rates</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>üí∞ Cost Savings</h3>
          <p><strong>Reduced bandwidth costs</strong> and pay-per-use pricing instead of reserved capacity.</p>
          <p class="impact">Impact: 70-90% cost reduction vs traditional cloud for many workloads</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>üîê Privacy & Compliance</h3>
          <p><strong>Keep data local</strong> to meet regulatory requirements (GDPR, CCPA, data residency laws).</p>
          <p class="impact">Impact: Easier compliance, reduced legal risk, customer trust</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>‚ö° Reliability</h3>
          <p><strong>Distributed system</strong> means if one location fails, 299+ others still work.</p>
          <p class="impact">Impact: Better uptime, automatic failover, DDoS resistance</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>üöÄ Scalability</h3>
          <p><strong>Infinite horizontal scaling</strong> across global edge locations automatically.</p>
          <p class="impact">Impact: Handle traffic spikes without pre-provisioning</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>üåç Global by Default</h3>
          <p><strong>Deploy once</strong>, run everywhere without managing multiple regions.</p>
          <p class="impact">Impact: Simpler operations, truly global reach instantly</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

