          <p>Edge functions usually have strict time limits (often 30 seconds max).</p>
          <p class="solution">Solution: Design for fast operations, queue long tasks for central cloud</p>
        </div>

        <div class="challenge">
          <h3>üíæ Memory Limits</h3>
          <p>Edge nodes are lightweight, can't run massive ML models on every edge.</p>
          <p class="solution">Solution: Use model distillation, inference at regional cloud when needed</p>
        </div>

        <div class="challenge">
          <h3>üóÑÔ∏è Statelessness</h3>
          <p>Edge is ephemeral. Can't rely on local storage between requests.</p>
          <p class="solution">Solution: Use durable storage services (KV, D1), design stateless operations</p>
        </div>

        <div class="challenge">
          <h3>üåç Deployment Complexity</h3>
          <p>Managing code across 300+ locations requires different skills than central deployment.</p>
